00:00:18.020 --> 00:00:20.030 position:56%
&gt;&gt; David Mao: Good morning everyone.

00:00:20.030 --> 00:00:23.640
My name is David Mao and I have
the privilege and honor of serving

00:00:23.640 --> 00:00:25.870 position:56%
as the Acting Librarian of Congress.

00:00:25.870 --> 00:00:28.240
So first off, welcome to
the Library of Congress,

00:00:28.240 --> 00:00:30.510
the world's largest library

00:00:30.510 --> 00:00:35.110
and our nation's first
federal cultural institution.

00:00:35.110 --> 00:00:37.900
Here at the Library of Congress,
we recognize the importance

00:00:37.900 --> 00:00:44.140
of all types of diversity and how
diverse cultures enrich our nation.

00:00:44.140 --> 00:00:47.600
So I'm very honored this morning
to open this special program

00:00:47.600 --> 00:00:50.830
which also celebrates the 200th
anniversary of the arrival

00:00:50.830 --> 00:00:56.970 position:56%
of Laurent Clerc and Thomas Hopkins
Gallaudet to America in August 1816.

00:00:56.970 --> 00:01:01.750
I understand that nine months after
their arrival, the first school

00:01:01.750 --> 00:01:03.900
for the deaf was founded
in Hartford, Connecticut

00:01:03.900 --> 00:01:08.510
and then 48 years after that,
Gallaudet University here

00:01:08.510 --> 00:01:10.420
in our own Washington, DC.

00:01:10.420 --> 00:01:13.790
It became the first school
for the advanced education

00:01:13.790 --> 00:01:16.780
of the deaf and hard of hearing.

00:01:16.780 --> 00:01:20.660
So today's program is cosponsored
by the Library of Congress Center

00:01:20.660 --> 00:01:23.340
for the Book and the
National Literacy--

00:01:23.340 --> 00:01:26.630
I'm sorry, National
Literary Society of the Deaf.

00:01:26.630 --> 00:01:28.310 position:56%
And it's all about opening the lines

00:01:28.310 --> 00:01:31.220
of communication among
the various deaf cultures

00:01:31.220 --> 00:01:34.160
and the libraries that serve them.

00:01:34.160 --> 00:01:37.880
The primary focus of course is to
build support for libraries to work

00:01:37.880 --> 00:01:41.480 position:56%
with organizations serving the deaf.

00:01:41.480 --> 00:01:45.500 position:56%
