Congress Deaf Association has served

00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:48.540
as a resource to, not
only the library

00:01:48.540 --> 00:01:51.220
but also the labor
organizations here to identify

00:01:51.220 --> 00:01:53.040
and eliminate discrimination--

00:01:53.040 --> 00:01:56.660
discriminatory policies
that affect deaf and hard

00:01:56.660 --> 00:02:00.140
of hearing employees here at
the Library of Congress and also

00:02:00.140 --> 00:02:05.970
to encourage the employment of
employees here at the library.

00:02:05.970 --> 00:02:10.240
The Library's Interpreting
Services Program, benefited here

00:02:10.240 --> 00:02:15.660
of course today by great
people, is part of the Office

00:02:15.660 --> 00:02:19.170
of Equal Employment Opportunity
and Diversity Programs

00:02:19.170 --> 00:02:23.570
