01:45:18.160 --> 01:45:24.150
down and create new works of art by
writing words on a piece of paper,

01:45:26.370 --> 01:45:32.380
that work can become
protected under copyright.

01:45:39.270 --> 01:45:42.920
So, you may be curious how it is
that you can protect your work

01:45:42.920 --> 01:45:47.520
and yourself when you
create these works of art.

01:45:47.520 --> 01:45:52.890
There are several processes that
we have, one being registration,

01:45:52.890 --> 01:46:01.300
and in my department, in
the recording department--

01:46:10.590 --> 01:46:12.290
-- is where we do that work.

01:46:12.290 --> 01:46:15.270
I would like to give
you some examples here--

01:46:20.410 --> 01:46:22.990
-- of useful works.

01:46:22.990 --> 01:46:30.000
A useful work is anything that
you create, it can be a machine,

01:46:30.000 --> 01:46:32.950
anything with a use--
with a moving part.

01:46:34.110 --> 01:46:42.560
So, for example, computers, mobile
phones, household appliances

01:46:42.560 --> 01:46:44.840
and other types of machinery.

01:46:44.840 --> 01:46:52.340
These all fall under the
category of useful works.

01:46:52.340 --> 01:46:54.630
These are things that you
can use for your self,

01:46:54.630 --> 01:46:56.570
for your own personal benefit.

01:46:56.570 --> 01:46:59.530
Things that are made
or manufactured.

01:47:04.490 --> 01:47:08.350
On the other hand, created--

01:47:08.350 --> 01:47:14.290
creative or intellectual
works incorporate things

01:47:14.290 --> 01:47:19.180
such as books, music and art.

01:47:20.740 --> 01:47:23.080
Jewelry also falls
into this category

01:47:23.080 --> 01:47:25.380
and many other things as well.

01:47:31.350 --> 01:47:36.360
So copyright is used to
protect these types of works.

01:47:40.870 --> 01:47:44.240
At the most simple or basic level--

01:47:50.460 --> 01:47:53.970
-- what do you think
copyright may mean to you?

01:47:57.990 --> 01:47:59.290
Imagine that you're at home

01:47:59.290 --> 01:48:02.850
and you're writing a
letter to your mother.

01:48:02.850 --> 01:48:07.330
The moment that you lift
the pen from the page,

01:48:07.330 --> 01:48:11.210
that letter becomes protected under
a copyright, it belongs to you.

01:48:11.210 --> 01:48:14.670
It means that it's your property.

01:48:14.670 --> 01:48:18.310
It can't belong to anyone
else, it can't belong to me

01:48:18.310 --> 01:48:23.110
and I have no rights to copy
that, nor does anyone else.

01:48:23.110 --> 01:48:26.170
That letter is your property.

01:48:26.170 --> 01:48:29.090
Now, through the registration
process here at the Library

01:48:29.090 --> 01:48:35.670
of Congress, that letter can
be registered as your property

01:48:35.670 --> 01:48:38.890
because it belongs to you.

01:48:38.890 --> 01:48:42.020
And if anyone wanted
to use that letter,

01:48:42.020 --> 01:48:45.790
they would be required
to get your permission.

01:48:48.950 --> 01:48:52.680
So, that then becomes
your right to copyright.

01:48:52.680 --> 01:48:58.430
So, in my department,
my responsibility is

01:48:58.430 --> 01:49:03.300
to provide citizens
certificates indicating

01:49:03.300 --> 01:49:08.280
that that property
actually belongs to you.

01:49:08.280 --> 01:49:11.430
And if that anyone wants
to steal your work,

01:49:11.430 --> 01:49:17.070
you would be legally protected
to sue that person for damages.

01:49:17.070 --> 01:49:28.320
So that puts that right
in black and white.

01:49:28.320 --> 01:49:31.400
So, there was a question
here in the audience.

01:49:37.310 --> 01:49:40.370
That's written down
in black and white.

01:49:40.370 --> 01:49:41.950
On a piece of paper, showing

01:49:41.950 --> 01:49:47.180
that this is your property,
that's correct.

01:49:47.180 --> 01:49:52.680
So, if you make jewelry, if you
take a picture of it and show it

01:49:52.680 --> 01:49:58.620
in the registration office here,
that will go into the certificate

01:49:58.620 --> 01:50:02.940
and into the copyright, rights
that are afforded to you.

01:50:07.060 --> 01:50:08.880
Now, this topic is very broad.

01:50:08.880 --> 01:50:11.980
I can only provide you with a
very surface level interpretation

01:50:11.980 --> 01:50:14.280
of what it means--

01:50:18.060 --> 01:50:20.860
-- because most of this
process involves a lot

01:50:20.860 --> 01:50:25.500
of legal obligation,
and I am no lawyer.

01:50:25.500 --> 01:50:30.970
So, my ability to explain the
process in depth is limited.

01:50:42.940 --> 01:50:47.340
Imagine, if you will, that you're
an actor and you write a play.

01:50:47.340 --> 01:50:55.660
That work belongs to you and
you therefore own the copyright.

01:51:09.550 --> 01:51:15.140
The works can be creative,
expressive, that can be poetry,

01:51:15.140 --> 01:51:22.120
song, art work, anything
that you see

01:51:22.120 --> 01:51:29.040
in picture format can be
protected under copyright.

01:51:29.040 --> 01:51:32.380
And I hope that's clear for you.

01:51:35.470 --> 01:51:36.770
Hopefully so.

01:51:36.770 --> 01:51:39.070
Great.

01:51:44.650 --> 01:51:48.100
Now, when you want to
register for a copyright--

01:51:53.020 --> 01:51:56.460
-- your copyright will actually
have a very long lifespan.

01:52:00.600 --> 01:52:05.690
In fact, that copyright
can last over 70 years.

01:52:05.690 --> 01:52:10.940
And anyone who wants to use that
work will require your permission

01:52:10.940 --> 01:52:16.510
without exception, otherwise,
that would be considered stealing.

01:52:16.510 --> 01:52:28.630
[ Inaudible Remark ]

01:52:28.630 --> 01:52:32.900
Question from the audience, when
is the copyright no longer valid?

01:52:37.320 --> 01:52:39.110
That's a very good question.

01:52:39.110 --> 01:52:46.730
I can't say for sure,
because I know, first of all,

01:52:46.730 --> 01:52:48.980
that it is over 70 years.

01:52:48.980 --> 01:52:53.860
But you can add periods of 25

01:52:53.860 --> 01:52:55.940
or 50 years depending
on the circumstances.

01:52:55.940 --> 01:52:59.710
So, it can go on for
a very long time.

01:53:04.080 --> 01:53:09.660 position:56%
So, in the same way that patents can
be extended, copyright can as well.

01:53:18.710 --> 01:53:22.480 position:56%
Question from the audience, can that
be passed down to a family member

01:53:22.480 --> 01:53:25.570
since it's the person's property?

01:53:31.440 --> 01:53:37.570
My understanding is that, through
a legal process, you can do that.

01:53:37.570 --> 01:53:41.790
But no one else has the right to
use your work unless that is--

01:53:41.790 --> 01:53:45.430
that happens because
your name is on it.

01:53:45.430 --> 01:53:53.230
So, is it a lifetime copyright?

01:53:55.090 --> 01:53:58.090
That's the answer.

01:53:58.090 --> 01:54:00.550
Another question from the audience.

01:54:00.550 --> 01:54:07.160 position:56%
&gt;&gt; When you have a copyright,
essentially, that copyright can last

01:54:07.160 --> 01:54:11.370
for over 70 years or
