01:54:11.370 --> 01:54:17.380
There is a book, for example,
if it is under a copyright,

01:54:17.380 --> 01:54:22.460
then that book, in theory,
can be yours forever?

01:54:22.460 --> 01:54:23.940
&gt;&gt; Chaim Levinson: Yes.

01:54:23.940 --> 01:54:34.360
It will last, unless you
decide, through a legal process,

01:54:34.360 --> 01:54:40.500
that your wishes are otherwise
and you make that very clear

01:54:40.500 --> 01:54:42.270
that you would allow another use.

01:54:42.270 --> 01:54:49.280 position:56%
But yes, it would continue but
there's a time in which it would end

01:54:49.280 --> 01:54:53.150
and become what is called,
in the public domain.

01:54:53.150 --> 01:55:00.860
And what that means is that at that
point, anyone is free to use it.

01:55:01.950 --> 01:55:06.640
So, yes, your copyright can
be renewed but you have to go

01:55:06.640 --> 01:55:11.710
through the correct legal
processes to do that.

01:55:11.710 --> 01:55:15.750
&gt;&gt; So, is there any time
limit to a copyright?

01:55:19.060 --> 01:55:21.820
&gt;&gt; Chaim Levinson: Not as
long as you're living, no.

01:55:21.820 --> 01:55:28.510
That property belongs
to you and you alone.

01:55:28.510 --> 01:55:35.460
[ Inaudible Remark ]

01:55:35.460 --> 01:55:41.270
&gt;&gt; And if the copyright legal owner
passes away then they can pass

01:55:41.270 --> 01:55:43.570
that right on to someone else?

01:55:46.390 --> 01:55:49.650
&gt;&gt; Chaim Levinson: Again,
through legal methods, yes.

01:55:55.810 --> 01:55:59.060
&gt;&gt; What about material
that's put online?

01:55:59.060 --> 01:56:01.600
Do the same rights apply?

01:56:04.650 --> 01:56:08.440 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Chaim Levinson: Now, that
question is actually beyond my role.

01:56:08.440 --> 01:56:11.670
As I said, I'm able to talk
about the copyright process

01:56:11.670 --> 01:56:14.160
on a rather surface level.

01:56:14.160 --> 01:56:16.930
But any questions that go beyond

01:56:16.930 --> 01:56:21.760
