03:24:05.490 --> 03:24:14.320
On Tuesday, June 18th 1816,
Laurent Clerc is traveling

03:24:14.320 --> 03:24:16.760
to America with Gallaudet.

03:24:21.880 --> 03:24:25.570
The name of the ship
is Mary Augusta.

03:24:25.570 --> 03:24:29.270
It's a rather small ship.

03:24:29.270 --> 03:24:38.260 position:56%
As we enter the boat you see six
individuals, two of which are French

03:24:38.260 --> 03:24:42.260
and four of which are American.

03:24:42.260 --> 03:24:45.190
One of the French men
seems to be unhappy.

03:24:45.190 --> 03:24:48.830
And the reason is well,
there's no communication

03:24:48.830 --> 03:24:53.870 position:56%
and this person doesn't know English
so, he's out of conversation then.

03:25:02.590 --> 03:25:04.150
All passports are checked
to make sure

03:25:04.150 --> 03:25:07.520
that they can go on their voyage.

03:25:24.270 --> 03:25:26.570
Here, we see the deck on the ship.

03:25:26.570 --> 03:25:34.220
And inside the ship we have a
cabin where daily prayers was held.

03:25:34.220 --> 03:25:38.690
We have our routine there in the
morning, afternoon and the evening.

03:25:47.550 --> 03:25:55.010
Upon standing on the deck you
see the glorious ocean there.

03:25:55.010 --> 03:25:58.980
And afterwards go back down
to the cabin, do some reading,

03:25:58.980 --> 03:26:00.970
go back to the daily routine.

03:26:00.970 --> 03:26:05.970
All in all, the trip
took about 52 days.

03:26:18.360 --> 03:26:26.110
Laurent Clerc, a French gentlemen
looking at Gallaudet, an American,

03:26:26.110 --> 03:26:29.190
language, culture was exchanged.

03:26:30.620 --> 03:26:33.810
So I learned English
being a Frenchmen knowing

03:26:33.810 --> 03:26:40.960
that I have quite a
long journey ahead of me

03:26:40.960 --> 03:26:45.240
and I'm not fluent in English.

03:26:45.240 --> 03:26:50.320
So, as I'm being taught,
I also teach.

03:27:03.340 --> 03:27:07.880
Before eating, of course,
washing of the hands,

03:27:07.880 --> 03:27:15.250 position:56%
making sure that you're well
groomed, appear to be taken care of,

03:27:15.250 --> 03:27:22.960
prayer, tea, nightly
readings and an array of food

03:27:22.960 --> 03:27:25.910
as well as water and wine.

03:27:41.060 --> 03:27:43.530
Again, knowing no English,
I'll try my best

03:27:43.530 --> 03:27:47.700
to learn English language asking
Thomas get question after question.

03:27:47.700 --> 03:27:51.970
One month into the voyage.

03:27:58.130 --> 03:28:04.710
I noticed that fluency in the
language is picking up quite fast.

03:28:04.710 --> 03:28:07.480
Almost as fast as the
ship is traveling

03:28:13.210 --> 03:28:14.510
And this exchange of language

03:28:14.510 --> 03:28:17.970
and culture takes place
everyday on this journey.

03:28:30.930 --> 03:28:35.580 position:56%
On the ship, while the gentlemen are
exchanging stories, a man is spotted

03:28:35.580 --> 03:28:38.040
on the shroud of the ship.

03:28:39.270 --> 03:28:43.800
Captain, a gentlemen on
the shroud is prohibited.

03:28:49.460 --> 03:28:55.510
A letter is given to the
captain and the captain laughs

03:28:55.510 --> 03:28:59.810
because in is his mind, being
on the shroud isn't prohibited.

03:29:03.290 --> 03:29:07.620
Clerc responds, on the ship that
I boarded, it was prohibited to be

03:29:07.620 --> 03:29:13.250
on the shroud when I was
traveling from France to England.

03:29:13.250 --> 03:29:17.430
It appears that you allow
that, quite different.

03:29:21.330 --> 03:29:24.260
Friday, June 21st.

03:29:28.350 --> 03:29:32.890
Looking back at how far I've come,
picking up this English language,

03:29:32.890 --> 03:29:37.070
riding back and forth in
English day in and day out.

03:29:37.070 --> 03:29:41.390
There's nothing else to do aside

03:29:41.390 --> 03:29:45.770
from observe the waves
crashing as I'm aboard the ship.

03:29:49.710 --> 03:29:52.260
June 22nd.

03:29:52.260 --> 03:29:56.170
Gallaudet explains
the American culture.

03:29:57.210 --> 03:30:00.410
So, that's what American
culture is like, I say to myself.

03:30:11.010 --> 03:30:15.260
Every Sunday, we respect the
tradition of the Sabbath.

03:30:15.260 --> 03:30:17.950
And every Sunday, there
would be sermons

03:30:17.950 --> 03:30:22.580
and those sermons will be
preached to the crew on the ship.

03:30:22.580 --> 03:30:29.370
And me being deaf, I
wasn't able to hear that.

03:30:29.370 --> 03:30:32.450
So, written sermon is
given to me instead.

03:30:32.450 --> 03:30:34.140
I look at the dictionary
doing my best

03:30:34.140 --> 03:30:36.780
to follow what everyone
else is following.

03:30:40.760 --> 03:30:45.280
Treacherous waters
calmed by the sermon.

03:30:46.640 --> 03:30:49.210
Prayer, serenity.

03:30:55.890 --> 03:31:00.540
The next night, bouts of
sea sickness, not for me

03:31:00.540 --> 03:31:03.970
but for others I observe on
the ship, including Gallaudet.

03:31:07.400 --> 03:31:11.730
As someone who frequents the ship,
sea sickness doesn't affect me

03:31:11.730 --> 03:31:16.300
but I'm not able to sleep
with the ship rocking back

03:31:16.300 --> 03:31:19.420
and forth, I lie restless.

03:31:21.630 --> 03:31:25.510
Finally, in the early hour
of five in the morning,

03:31:25.510 --> 03:31:30.580
I'm able to fall sleep and
shortly after, I'm woken up.

03:31:30.580 --> 03:31:34.240
Painfully, I get up out the bed.

03:31:34.240 --> 03:31:38.580
Going to eat breakfast,
morning prayer,

03:31:38.580 --> 03:31:40.890
stand on the deck and observe.

03:31:49.280 --> 03:31:54.690
I recall Gallaudet mentioning
Alice Cogswell and his desire

03:31:54.690 --> 03:31:57.070
for all of us to meet together.

03:32:06.150 --> 03:32:10.230
It just so happened
that once upon a time,

03:32:10.230 --> 03:32:14.490
we actually had crossed paths
and I wasn't even aware.

03:32:28.990 --> 03:32:34.330
Conversations with the crew ensue,
letters written back and forth.

03:32:42.020 --> 03:32:44.810 position:56%
Is my wife deaf and dumb, I'm asked.

03:32:44.810 --> 03:32:51.050
And my response, of course,
we share the same suffering.

03:32:51.050 --> 03:32:52.920
We share the same challenges.

03:32:52.920 --> 03:32:58.380
June 27th.

03:33:02.710 --> 03:33:07.980
Another day of entries on
my battery and I'm shocked

03:33:07.980 --> 03:33:10.050
to see crews screaming,
there's a monster

03:33:10.050 --> 03:33:12.780
in the ocean, monster in the ocean.

03:33:12.780 --> 03:33:16.230
After looking in the
ocean and seeing nothing,

03:33:16.230 --> 03:33:20.130
I thought to myself,
perhaps it was a whale.

03:33:31.340 --> 03:33:35.020
I recall Gallaudet continuing
to help my English skills,

03:33:35.020 --> 03:33:37.880
helping me with my writing.

03:33:44.400 --> 03:33:49.000
I recall being praised
for my ability to pick

03:33:49.000 --> 03:33:51.010
up the English language
by Gallaudet.

03:33:51.010 --> 03:33:55.410
All this time we're on the
ocean, I'm doing my best.

03:33:56.450 --> 03:33:59.730
Other members on the crew realizing
that I've made some progress

03:33:59.730 --> 03:34:02.870
and they make comments about that.

03:34:08.920 --> 03:34:14.370 position:56%
Throughout our voyage, Gallaudet and
I are talking about ideas on setting

03:34:14.370 --> 03:34:17.230
up a school for the deaf.

03:34:17.230 --> 03:34:18.530
What should we do?

03:34:18.530 --> 03:34:19.830
What's the best way to go about it?

03:34:19.830 --> 03:34:25.840 position:56%
What would be the age of these
students at the school for the deaf?

03:34:25.840 --> 03:34:30.310
Often, parents don't want to let go
of their kids at such a young age.

03:34:30.310 --> 03:34:37.540
That's something we
had to think about.

03:34:37.540 --> 03:34:39.050
How long will they be in school?

03:34:39.050 --> 03:34:41.350
Another consideration.

03:34:45.170 --> 03:34:46.550
Perhaps, for those who are coming

03:34:46.550 --> 03:34:49.260
from wealthy families,
they'll stay longer.

03:34:55.220 --> 03:34:57.520
June 30th.

03:35:05.010 --> 03:35:10.130
I recall the design of the ship
with a gentleman standing there

03:35:10.130 --> 03:35:17.950
and just barely gets missed by
a part on the ship that falls

03:35:17.950 --> 03:35:22.600
from the shroud, just
barely missing him.

03:35:32.420 --> 03:35:40.280
Duck, chicken, pig,
canary, the canary was not

03:35:40.280 --> 03:35:42.580
for eating, don't be fooled.

03:35:44.140 --> 03:35:49.230
It was only for song purposes, to
listen to the joys of the music.

03:35:52.420 --> 03:35:59.680
I recall a hog and
slaughtered, coming nauseous,

03:35:59.680 --> 03:36:03.210
avoiding the deck what-- with
all the blood being spilled.

03:36:03.210 --> 03:36:07.970
Quiet a traumatizing experience.

03:36:12.840 --> 03:36:16.510 position:56%
Perhaps an experience best withheld.

03:36:16.510 --> 03:36:23.510
[ Laughter ]

